article.description: Aaron Brennan scored 11 points and made key free throws late to help IUPUI hold off Green Bay for a 67-63 victory on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Aaron Brennan's late FTs help IUPUI hold off Green Bay 67-63
article.linkText: Aaron Brennan's late FTs help IUPUI hold off Green Bay 67-63
article.story: ASHWAUBENON, Wis. -- Aaron Brennan scored 11 points and made key free throws late to help IUPUI hold off Green Bay for a 67-63 victory on Tuesday night. IUPUI (4-10, 1-2 Horizon League) had a 61-53 lead with 1:55 to play. Sandy Cohen III made a pair of free throws, David Jesperson hit a jumper and PJ Pipes converted a 3-point play during a 7-1 surge to pull Green Bay (7-9, 2-1) to 62-60 with 36 seconds left. Brennan then made 3 of 4 from the line and T.J. Henderson added a layup to seal it. Henderson had 13 points to lead the Jaguars. Nick Rogers added 11 points and Evan Hall chipped in 10 points with 10 rebounds. Khalil Small scored 18 points for Green Bay, which missed 16 of 17 3-point attempts. Pipes finished with 15 points and Cohen had 14.
